Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.61,0:00:04.49,English,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.49,0:00:09.22,English,,0,0,0,,Let me show you how rockets travel in space even there is no air to fly on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.22,0:00:13.73,English,,0,0,0,,Rockets have engines that push out a lot of material at very high speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.73,0:00:19.60,English,,0,0,0,,According to Newton Third Law, for every action, there's a equal and opposite reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.60,0:00:22.23,English,,0,0,0,,So for example, if you're pushing the wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.23,0:00:25.38,English,,0,0,0,,The wall can push you back with the exact same force.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.38,0:00:27.12,English,,0,0,0,,That's why nothing moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.12,0:00:29.73,English,,0,0,0,,Here, I have a mouse trap that is put on the LEGO wheels,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.73,0:00:31.41,English,,0,0,0,,so, (it) can move around easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.68,0:00:38.45,English,,0,0,0,,Let me trigger it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.37,0:00:44.69,English,,0,0,0,,See, it stays around the same area.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.69,0:00:46.92,English,,0,0,0,,I have take three marbles together
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.92,0:00:49.86,English,,0,0,0,,to put on the back of the mousetrap, for it to do them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.94,0:01:00.19,English,,0,0,0,,See, the marble shoot that way and the mousetrap jumps the other way as the reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.19,0:01:05.24,English,,0,0,0,,Similarly in space, our rockets has to shoot a ton of burning gas, (which is) very fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.24,0:01:08.08,English,,0,0,0,,And in reaction, the rocket is pushed forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.08,0:01:10.86,English,,0,0,0,,AND YOU DON'T NEED ANY AIR FOR THIS TO HAPPEN.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.04,0:01:15.86,English,,0,0,0,,So in vacuum space, the rocket should moves forward. The end:-)
